The paper discusses secure multipath routing and the use of machine learning techniques to determine the security threat level along each path. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The use of compressed sensing for optimal sampling and compression of network data suggests a focus on efficient data processing, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses information assurance levels, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE).
